#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.42"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.42:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.42:0.2"
msgid "5. Muṇḍarājavagga"
msgstr "5. With King Muṇḍa"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.42:0.3"
msgid "42. Sappurisasutta"
msgstr "42. A Good Person"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.42:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Sappuriso, bhikkhave, kule jāyamāno bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya "
"hoti;"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a good person is born in a family for the benefit, welfare, and "
"happiness of the people."

#. VAR: mātāpitūnaṃ → mātāpitunnaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.42:1.2"
msgid "mātāpitūnaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti;"
msgstr "For the benefit, welfare, and happiness of mother and father;"

msgctxt "an5.42:1.3"
msgid "puttadārassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti;"
msgstr "children and partners;"

msgctxt "an5.42:1.4"
msgid "dāsakammakaraporisassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti;"
msgstr "bondservants, workers, and staff;"

msgctxt "an5.42:1.5"
msgid "mittāmaccānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti;"
msgstr "friends and colleagues;"

msgctxt "an5.42:1.6"
msgid "samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti."
msgstr "and ascetics and brahmins."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.47"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.42:2.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāmegho sabbasassāni sampādento bahuno janassa "
"atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a great rain cloud, which nourishes all the crops for the benefit, "
"welfare, and happiness of the people."

msgctxt "an5.42:2.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sappuriso kule jāyamāno bahuno janassa atthāya "
"hitāya sukhāya hoti;"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a good person is born in a family for the benefit, welfare, "
"and happiness of the people. …"

msgctxt "an5.42:2.3"
msgid "mātāpitūnaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.42:2.4"
msgid "puttadārassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.42:2.5"
msgid "dāsakammakaraporisassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.42:2.6"
msgid "mittāmaccānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.42:2.7"
msgid "samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hotīti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.42:3.1"
msgid "Hito bahunnaṃ paṭipajja bhoge,"
msgstr "The gods protect one who is guarded by principle,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:3.2"
msgid "Taṃ devatā rakkhati dhammaguttaṃ;"
msgstr "who uses their wealth for the welfare of the many."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:3.3"
msgid "Bahussutaṃ sīlavatūpapannaṃ,"
msgstr "One who is learned, with precepts and observances intact,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: vijahati → vijahāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.42:3.4"
msgid "Dhamme ṭhitaṃ na vijahati kitti."
msgstr "and steady in principle, doesn’t lose their reputation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.42:4.1"
msgid "Dhammaṭṭhaṃ sīlasampannaṃ,"
msgstr "Firm in principle, accomplished in ethical conduct,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:4.2"
msgid "saccavādiṃ hirīmanaṃ;"
msgstr "a speaker of truth, and conscientious,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:4.3"
msgid "Nekkhaṃ jambonadasseva,"
msgstr "like a coin of mountain gold:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:4.4"
msgid "ko taṃ ninditumarahati;"
msgstr "who is worthy of criticizing them?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:4.5"
msgid "Devāpi naṃ pasaṃsanti,"
msgstr "Even the gods praise them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:4.6"
msgid "brahmunāpi pasaṃsito”ti."
msgstr "and by Brahmā, too, they’re praised.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.42:4.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
